Quote: The so called road between French's & Barriball's clearing ...[sic] is really the worst part of the line as it is so thickly overgrown [96] with makos &c. The tracks were destroyed by the pigs but there were still traces [of Maori] - one a mako stick cut, & others some hairs of a mat caught in a stick.
Notes: (A.S. Atkinson)

